* Editor's note: This live event will be broadcast live on eNCA.com and is expected to start at 11am.JOHANNESBURG - Former SABC COO Hlaudi Motsoeneng will hold a media briefing on Wednesday to address matters relating to his tenure at the public broadcaster.Last year, the Western Cape High Court ruled that Motsoeneng s appointment was irrational and unlawful.READ: Hlaudi Motsoeneng has 'no mandate' to speak for SABC: DAThe court further ruled that Motsoeneng should not hold any position at the SABC.Despite this, Motosoeneng is expected to speak on -- among other things -- the new SABC board members, the Multichoice contract and the SABC s financial status between 2012 and 2016.eNCA